Definition at line 1206 of file srm_types.h.

typedef void* SRM_Object_Reference
 

TYPEDEF: SRM_Object_Reference

An Object_Reference is an opaque non-object data type that allows an application to reliably access an instance of an object. Object_References may be compared for equality and tested to see if they are equal to the special value NULL_Object. If two Object_References are equal, they refer to the same object instance. In all the method specifications in the API clause of 18026, whenever an argument passed to or returned from a method is an object, it is an object reference that is passed.
